Brand New: H&K P30SK 9mm DA/SA with NIght Sights and De-Cocker
The subcompact model of the renowned P30 handgun, P30SK (SubKompact) series has all of the sought-after characteristics of the larger frame P30 and P30L pistols but in a more concealable design.
The completely adjustable P30 grip feature — consisting of interchangeable backstraps and lateral grip panels — is replicated in the ultra-compact grip frame of the P30SK. This allows the pistol to be easily modified to fit to any individual user.
Other trigger modes include conventional double action/single action (DA/SA) with a serrated de-cocking button located on the rear of the frame. The DA/SA mode is available with and without dual ambidextrous manual safeties located on the left and right side of the frame. Other ambidextrous controls include dual slide and magazine release levers. Like all P30 pistols, the P30SK features an automatic hammer safety and firing pin safety.
An abbreviated Picatinny rail molded into the front of the frame enables weapon lights, lasers, or other accessories to be easily mounted. All P30SK models have been extensively tested during a three year development process.
Despite their small size, P30SK subcompacts have excellent weight and balance making them naturally pointable, easy to control, and accurate to shoot; currently available in 9 mm.

title: For Sale:  Winchester Model 99 Thumb Trigger Rifle - .22 (Very Unique)
postcontent: This listing is for a Winchester Thumb Trigger - Model 99, which is an adaptation of the Winchester model 1902. This particular model does not have an ordinary trigger, instead this trigger is extended towards the rear of the gun beneath the firing pin. This rifle is in full working condition, and is fired by depressing the trigger on top with your thumb. It is chambered for .22LR, & .22 Short. From what I understand, this was the only Winchester ever made with a thumb trigger, and their first rifle listed with a rebounding lock. They made approximately 75,000 of these and many were shipped to Australia.  They were made between 1904 - 1923 and none of them had a serial number. If you have questions, please ask, if you want a specific picture from another angle or better lighting, please ask. This was passed down to me by my father who fortunately took very good care of it. I hope to allow someone else to enjoy it that truly appreciates the gun, that in my opinion is a very unique and interesting find for the avid collector.  Thanks for your interest!
